DOM (Document Object Model)

--It is a programming interface in the web development that allows us to interact and manipulate(change) with the html documents.
---When the webpage is loaded the browser will create the DOM of the web page

When an html file is loaded into the browser, the java script cannot understand the html document directly

DOM: is basically the representation of same html document but in the  tree-like structure composed of objects

Html Dom allows JavaScript to access(to get) and modify the elements in the Html document

Key points:
1)Structure: The DOM represents the structure of Html document as tree; each node in a tree represents the element ,an attribute, text
2)Manipulation: using js,you can interact with elements(buttons) we can modify, add ,remove the elements
3)Event Handling
4)W3C-World Wide Web Consortium

<html>
<head>
<title> college </college>
</head>
<body>
<h1 iam in hyd </h1>


</body>

</html>

-- in DOM all the elements are defined objects
property: is a value that you can set to the objects(like changing content of an html element)
Method: an action
(I like add or delete)

Methods of DOM:
getting element
1)getting an element by id
2)getting an element by class
3)getting an element by tag name
4)getting an element by query selector

<style>
    h1.b {
